Class PrioritizedAsyncTask<T>

java.lang.Object
  android.os.AsyncTask<Void,Void,T>
      com.burstly.lib.util.PrioritizedAsyncTask<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
SafeAsyncTask, SequentAsyncTask
public abstract class PrioritizedAsyncTask<T>
extends AsyncTask<Void,Void,T>

This class supports custom priorities based on Process class for working thread. The original thread's priority being saved before invoking performInBackground() and restored afterwards. This is done to eliminate priority influence on global AsyncTask thread pool.

Author:
Alexey Redinskii
